f=Product/DEPARTMENT-WORKFLOW.md · h1:Product — Department Workflow=**Built 2026-07-10 (all agents complete).** Owner: CTO Product role. Law: **Evidence Gate** (enforced spec; separate charter Engineering Security Charter Fleet Charter senior). Plan: `PRODUCT-REDESIGN-PLAN.md`. · s=Product decides WHAT gets built proves worth building. Five agents: **spec** defines (evidence-gated PRDs, quinn-testable criteria), **ux** discovers (reuse-first research voice-of-customer), **loom** experiments (riskiest-first, frozen criteria, PMF reads), **metric** measures (versioned metric truth, verified instruments), **price** monetizes (WTP packaging governed changes). One signature rule binds them: **no evidence, backlog entry; criteria, build; measurement, "shipped."** · h2:Working structure agents, pods=\| Pod \| Agent \| One-line job \| · h2:Working structure agents, pods=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Working structure agents, pods=\| Definition \| **spec** ⭐ \| the Evidence Gate: opportunity → evidence-cited PRD → RICE backlog → frozen handoff \| · h2:Working structure agents, pods=\| Discovery \| **ux**, **loom** \| evidence supply (research repo + VoC) and hypothesis testing (experiments + PMF) \| · h2:Working structure agents, pods=\| Measurement \| **metric** \| the single metric truth: versioned definitions, funnels, verified instruments \| · h2:Working structure agents, pods=\| Monetization \| **price** 🆕 \| willingness-to-pay → packaging → governed price changes (board on locked commitments) \| · h2:Working structure agents, pods=leader (identity: evidence-first-discoverer, archetype-only). new catalog. · h2:Working tree evidence loop=`ux (research repo + voice-of-customer) ──┐ \· metric (metric truth + funnel reads) ────┼─► spec's intake gate (backlog-rules: cite or bounce) \· loom (experiment verdicts + PMF reads) ──┘            │ \· ▼ \· opportunity-assessment → PRD (criteria quinn can test)` · h2:Working instructions=**No evidence, backlog entry.** backlog item cites research (ux repo IDs), metrics (metric@vN reads), experiment verdict (loom registry). spec's backlog-rules bounces uncited items; Confidence capped evidence ladder (RICE flagged rubric, rule 0.6). **Query before you produce.** queries research repository before any new study; loom queries experiment registry before any new test; metric reuses versioned definitions before minting new ones fleet never unknowingly re-runs settled work (scout's adopt-reject pattern, three homes). **Criteria frozen before build before data.** PRD acceptance criteria written testable-at-quinn's-gate frozen (echo-confirmed); experiment decision rules success criteria frozen before running; bar moved after seeing results result. **Measurement precondition, afterthought.** experiment runs until metric verifies instruments fire live; "shipped" measurement event (metric reads outcome), deploy event (ops owns deploys). MISSING beats interpolated everywhere. **Monetization never moves silently.** Existing customers never silently repriced test (new/holdout only) change (governed, grandfathered, customer-favorable). change touching Governance locked commitment routes board; until Governance's docs exist, queues (most-restrictive default). **Product supplies evidence; leaders decide.** PMF verdicts, priorities, pivots route marcus/vista (Executive Office); spec never publishes rival roadmap; loom never makes double-down/pivot call; metric/ux/price measure research, they don't decide product move. **The exhaust anneals.** shipped-but-missed item baseline failure skill's text spec's templates, ux's synthesis, loom's assumptions; overturned findings/verdicts route anneal board (Fleet Charter Rail skill lessons. · h2:Cross-department boundaries (share, don't duplicate)=**spec quinn (Engineering):** spec owns WHAT passes (acceptance criteria), quinn owns WHETHER passed; echo-confirmed ways., **spec vista (Executive Office):** vista owns company roadmap; spec feeds per-product evidence, receives priorities., **metric kai (Brand Studio):** metric owns in-product behavior; kai owns campaign/brand attribution; shared reads cite owner's number; signup event seam., **metric river (future Data Analytics):** definitions sync versioned export interface, binding dept builds., **loom proto/forge (AI Agents):** one experiment discipline, different subjects loom tests product hypotheses users, proto tests agents cage, forge benchmarks models; loom's registry mirrors scout's adopt-reject., **ux Client Success (future):** voice-of-customer intake read-only support pipeline., **price board (Governance):** locked-commitment-touching changes gate board; changes logged proposals. **price felix/Finance (future):** price sets price, finance owns margin/treasury., **ux/loom/price Behavioral Science (future):** bias/persuasion theory dept's flagged dependency, inlined., **All agents:** Fleet Charter binds (registered tools only, board-gated skill changes anneal); gauge scorecards agents like any others. · h2:Department status=\| Agent \| Pod \| Skills \| Identity \| Operational \| Logical \| agent.md \| · h2:Department status=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Department status=\| spec \| Definition \| 4/4 (+ rice.py, tested) \| evidence-first-discoverer (leader) \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · h2:Department status=\| metric \| Measurement \| 4/4 (+ sample_size.py, tested) \| empty (non-leader) \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · h2:Department status=\| ux \| Discovery \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · h2:Department status=\| loom \| Discovery \| 4/4 \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · h2:Department status=\| price \| Monetization \| 4/4 (new agent) \| empty \| 5/5 \| placeholder \| current \| · h2:Department status=Department complete 2026-07-10 (spec metric built prior session; metric finished ux/loom/price built session after Fable-5 interruption). Standing pending: · h2:Department status=**Operator decisions** (PRODUCT-REDESIGN-PLAN): price confirmed (built); spec identity archetype-only (built); price→board locked-commitments gate confirmed; voice-of-customer sources business (`<FILL_IN>` idles honestly without them); scout run queued marketplace searches (user-story-mapping, usability-testing, jtbd-interviews, aarrr, lean-experimentation)., **Product profiles** business (`<FILL_IN>`: NSM, personas, funnel stages, price floors, locked-commitment refs)., **Logical source books:** shared statistics/experimentation text (buy once metric/ux/loom gauge/forge/vista fleet-wide); pricing-economics text (price); retention/LTV source (loom/metric)., **Deferred bindings:** metric's export interface future Data Analytics (river); Governance gate price (board dormant until docs exist proposals queue); Behavioral Science dependency flagged across ux/loom/price.